body:
I thought the intent of introducing 'Unkonwn' host status was to replace the entire null semantics that was thought to be confusing in the investigators. By doing it partially aren't we introducing more confusion - now there is 'null' as well as 'Unknown' semantics.

Also specific to the change I see the below code removed
if (vmState == null) {continue;}

Shouldn't it be 
if (vmState == Status.Unknown) {continue;}
